CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, October 7, 1961, pg. 14 reads: "Children's Eat-A-Rama - The 7900 Block Club of Susquehanna St., recently closed out the summer and introduced fall to children of the block, by holding an old-fashioned cook-out at the home of Mr. and Mrs. Homer Wilson, the club's president. The joyous event, with fun, food, and prizes, was planned by the social chairman, Mrs. Carrie Garrett; the vice president, Mrs. Ann Mae Knox; and Mrs. Kate Moore. - Harris photo."
TitMainTitle: Group of men, women, and young boys and girls, including woman standing at grill placing hotdog in bun held by young girl, gathered on lawn of Mr. and Mrs. Homer Wilson, Susquehanna Street
